(Young Lord finds the wrong crush.)

34
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:18,850
Aren't you that...

35
00:02:19,449 --> 00:02:20,410
Heroine of Jianglin?

36
00:02:20,449 --> 00:02:21,729
What heroine?

37
00:02:22,929 --> 00:02:23,690
Get over there.

38
00:02:25,290 --> 00:02:26,209
What do you want?

39
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:34,530
Did they kidnap you?

40
00:02:35,130 --> 00:02:35,929
Kidnap me?

41
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:37,690
There's no such thing.

42
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:41,489
Since you're not kidnapped,

43
00:02:41,489 --> 00:02:42,290
let's go home.

44
00:02:42,329 --> 00:02:43,929
Father turned
the Lord's Mansion upside down.

45
00:02:44,169 --> 00:02:45,250
- What?
- What?

46
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:47,010
Who are you?

47
00:02:47,609 --> 00:02:48,530
And who are you?

48
00:02:48,690 --> 00:02:51,209
Come on, do you know who he is?

49
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:51,929
Wait.

50
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:53,530
They're my friends, brother.

51
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:54,810
- Brother?
- Brother?

52
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:55,889
Your friends?

53
00:02:56,329 --> 00:02:56,929
You know them?

54
00:02:58,130 --> 00:02:59,049
I was injured.

55
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:00,609
They've been taking care of me.

56
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:02,370
You got injured again?

57
00:03:02,370 --> 00:03:02,929
Where?

58
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:04,889
This guy is your big brother?

59
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:05,729
Yeah.

60
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:06,729
What about him?

61
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:08,288
He...

62
00:03:08,729 --> 00:03:10,090
He's our servant. Why?

63
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:12,449
Birds of a feather.

64
00:03:13,130 --> 00:03:15,530
Keling, you know each other?

65
00:03:16,810 --> 00:03:18,489
We're kind of like friends.

66
00:03:19,010 --> 00:03:19,889
Friends?

67
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:21,609
I'm not your friend.

68
00:03:21,649 --> 00:03:22,929
Chun Keling, what are you doing?

69
00:03:22,929 --> 00:03:24,010
What are you doing?

70
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:26,010
Don't block me. Put that away.

71
00:03:26,049 --> 00:03:27,090
Sorry, Your Highness.

72
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:28,769
My little daughter has no manners.

73
00:03:28,810 --> 00:03:29,850
Please forgive her.

74
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:30,889
It's okay.

75
00:03:30,970 --> 00:03:33,250
We're friends, after all.

76
00:03:37,609 --> 00:03:38,889
So you're friends.

77
00:03:38,929 --> 00:03:39,929
And you are...

78
00:03:41,169 --> 00:03:42,169
I didn't introduce myself.

79
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:45,970
I am the Young Lord
from Lord Ling's Mansion.

80
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:47,850
Young Lord.

81
00:03:50,489 --> 00:03:51,769
- Young Lord?
- Young Lord?

82
00:04:05,769 --> 00:04:07,449
We'd better go.

83
00:04:07,489 --> 00:04:08,530
Leave your friends alone.

84
00:04:29,690 --> 00:04:30,529
Young Lord.

85
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,449
Have some tea.

86
00:04:42,570 --> 00:04:44,170
Take this hairpin.

87
00:04:44,610 --> 00:04:46,889
Give it to the girl who makes you happy.

88
00:04:47,289 --> 00:04:49,449
Then she will make you even more joyful.

89
00:04:50,769 --> 00:04:51,449
Young Lord.

90
00:04:51,930 --> 00:04:54,730
It turns out that the girl
who pleases the Fourth Prince is here.

91
00:05:01,409 --> 00:05:02,810
When did you make up?

92
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:08,490
Young Lord.

93
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,610
We don't have fancy tea at home.

94
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:13,170
Please get by with it.

95
00:05:20,889 --> 00:05:22,050
It smells great.

96
00:05:22,329 --> 00:05:23,889
What is it?

97
00:05:24,170 --> 00:05:25,889
I-It's tea.

98
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:30,769
So it's tea.

99
00:05:30,769 --> 00:05:32,930
I thought it was...

100
00:05:32,969 --> 00:05:34,010
So it's tea...

101
00:05:34,969 --> 00:05:35,889
No wonder.

102
00:05:37,409 --> 00:05:38,889
We'd better go.

103
00:05:38,930 --> 00:05:40,289
Father is waiting for you at home.

104
00:05:41,930 --> 00:05:43,050
Young Lord.

105
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:44,329
You're leaving?

106
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:45,610
Won't you stay longer?

107
00:05:45,610 --> 00:05:47,209
Rain check.

108
00:05:49,649 --> 00:05:50,529
Young Lord.

109
00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:52,769
Sorry we didn't

110
00:05:52,849 --> 00:05:53,969
treat you well enough.

111
00:05:54,769 --> 00:05:55,889
You treated me very well.

112
00:05:58,289 --> 00:05:59,449
Young Lord.

113
00:06:00,529 --> 00:06:01,250
Come often.

114
00:06:01,329 --> 00:06:01,889
Of course.

115
00:06:01,889 --> 00:06:02,889
Let's go.

116
00:06:06,810 --> 00:06:07,769
Look at you.

117
00:06:07,810 --> 00:06:09,130
Can't you be discreet?

118
00:06:10,409 --> 00:06:11,089
Mother.

119
00:06:11,889 --> 00:06:13,570
I have to burn incense for Father.

120
00:06:14,010 --> 00:06:16,490
I bet it's Father manifesting this omen.

121
00:06:18,289 --> 00:06:19,449
Young Lord?

122
00:06:20,810 --> 00:06:23,490
Could it be that A-Si
is also His Highness's son?

123
00:06:35,889 --> 00:06:38,529
Chun Jinrong, why are you up so early?

124
00:06:39,849 --> 00:06:41,329
I'm not up early.

125
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:43,730
I stayed up all night.

126
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:45,089
Perfect.

127
00:06:45,409 --> 00:06:48,209
Have breakfast and come with me
to the Marriage Bridge

128
00:06:48,209 --> 00:06:49,449
to look for dates.

129
00:06:49,969 --> 00:06:51,529
We have the Young Lord coming.

130
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:53,329
Why would we go to the Marriage Bridge?

131
00:06:53,690 --> 00:06:54,969
Are you daydreaming?

132
00:06:55,769 --> 00:06:56,329
Mother.

133
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:59,329
I have this strong feeling.

134
00:06:59,649 --> 00:07:01,329
The Young Lord will be back.

135
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:03,649
I can't be away when he's here.

136
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,610
Wake up.

137
00:07:06,610 --> 00:07:07,969
Don't ruin my hairstyle.

138
00:07:08,209 --> 00:07:09,769
Chun Jinrong, be practical, okay?

139
00:07:10,289 --> 00:07:11,649
You're 30 and still single.

140
00:07:11,690 --> 00:07:12,649
Why is that?

141
00:07:12,889 --> 00:07:14,969
Isn't it because you're so picky?

142
00:07:15,209 --> 00:07:18,529
Mother, he's the Young Lord.

143
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:21,089
He may have seen His Majesty.

144
00:07:21,610 --> 00:07:22,449
Listen.

145
00:07:27,209 --> 00:07:29,449
Why did the Young Lord come to visit us?

146
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,409
Because I have a chance.

147
00:07:31,889 --> 00:07:32,810
You have a chance?

148
00:07:32,849 --> 00:07:34,329
Take a look in the mirror.

149
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,969
You think he may like you?

150
00:07:36,969 --> 00:07:37,570
I don't care.

151
00:07:37,769 --> 00:07:39,250
I'm going to wait here.

152
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:42,089
Fine, do as you wish.

153
00:07:42,449 --> 00:07:43,649
A thirty-year-old

154
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:44,969
can be so immature.

155
00:07:45,570 --> 00:07:47,370
And A-Si.

156
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:48,730
That kid

157
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,449
got me so mistaken.

158
00:07:50,490 --> 00:07:52,730
I thought his father was in jail.

159
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:56,089
When did he ever say that?

160
00:07:56,089 --> 00:07:57,649
Didn't he say it himself?

161
00:07:57,730 --> 00:07:59,849
His father stays
somewhere with many guards.

162
00:07:59,889 --> 00:08:00,889
The Lord's Mansion

163
00:08:00,969 --> 00:08:02,449
has many guards, of course.

164
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:05,010
You got it wrong all along.

165
00:08:05,089 --> 00:08:06,649
Fine.

166
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:09,370
It's all my fault.

167
00:08:09,409 --> 00:08:10,969
You did nothing wrong.

168
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,730
A-Are you coming with me later?

169
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:13,329
No.

170
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,329
Whatever.

171
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:15,570
I'm not going.

172
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:17,649
I'll wait for Young Lord here.

173
00:08:17,849 --> 00:08:18,570
Forever.

174
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:23,849
Mother, isn't Jinrong going to eat?

175
00:08:24,849 --> 00:08:25,649
Let her be.

176
00:08:26,649 --> 00:08:28,490
Pancake with preserved vegetables again?

177
00:08:28,529 --> 00:08:30,529
I saw some preserved vegetables left.

178
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:31,769
They may go bad.

179
00:08:34,730 --> 00:08:35,289
When...

180
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:36,370
did you cook the lotus root?

181
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:37,649
Two days ago?

182
00:08:39,809 --> 00:08:41,970
It's too hot. It must have gone sour.

183
00:08:42,010 --> 00:08:43,689
Don't eat it. Throw it away.

184
00:08:43,970 --> 00:08:44,889
No, Mother.

185
00:08:44,929 --> 00:08:46,450
I smelled it. It's just fine.

186
00:08:51,409 --> 00:08:52,529
Fine, I'm done.

187
00:08:52,610 --> 00:08:54,169
I'm going to the Marriage Bridge.

188
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:58,130
This is bad. Throw it away.

189
00:08:58,169 --> 00:08:58,889
Okay, Mother.

190
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:00,090
I'll throw it away.

191
00:09:06,409 --> 00:09:07,130
Peilan.

192
00:09:07,169 --> 00:09:08,169
Morning, Master.

193
00:09:08,169 --> 00:09:09,169
Morning.

194
00:09:09,330 --> 00:09:10,330
Have breakfast, Master.

195
00:09:10,330 --> 00:09:11,010
Okay.

196
00:09:11,049 --> 00:09:12,169
Thank you.

197
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:13,090
Here.

198
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:17,409
Morning, Peilan.

199
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:17,929
Banxia.

200
00:09:18,010 --> 00:09:18,889
Morning, Banxia.

201
00:09:22,490 --> 00:09:23,610
Preserved vegetable pancake.

202
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:25,929
Where did you find
the preserved vegetables?

203
00:09:25,929 --> 00:09:27,130
Didn't I throw them away?

204
00:09:27,409 --> 00:09:28,409
So it was you.

205
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:29,689
I took them back.

206
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:30,889
Why would you do that?

207
00:09:30,929 --> 00:09:32,809
I found molds in there
while drying herbs yesterday.

208
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:38,049
Don't eat it. It's moldy.

209
00:09:38,130 --> 00:09:39,130
It's fine.

210
00:09:39,169 --> 00:09:40,689
Preserved vegetables are fine.

211
00:09:40,769 --> 00:09:41,929
I've washed them well.

212
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,250
These vegetables are preserved,

213
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:45,330
not to be served when moldy.

214
00:09:45,330 --> 00:09:47,010
Peilan, it's common sense.

215
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:49,130
Peilan, I don't mean to criticize you.

216
00:09:49,169 --> 00:09:50,130
You're a good girl.

217
00:09:50,169 --> 00:09:52,010
You're just too frugal.

218
00:09:52,010 --> 00:09:53,490
What's wrong with that?

219
00:09:53,490 --> 00:09:55,610
But you can't be frugal
when it comes to food.

220
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:56,689
There shall be a limit.

221
00:09:56,769 --> 00:09:57,889
As the saying goes,

222
00:09:58,049 --> 00:09:59,529
"Illness finds its way in by the mouth."

223
00:09:59,529 --> 00:10:01,049
And another saying goes,

224
00:10:01,090 --> 00:10:02,169
"Run a thrifty household."

225
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:04,529
Everything costs us money.

226
00:10:04,529 --> 00:10:05,850
We must spend money wisely.

227
00:10:07,130 --> 00:10:08,289
Do as you wish.

228
00:10:09,090 --> 00:10:10,610
Let's eat out, Master.

229
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:15,689
Let's go.

230
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,210
Coming.

231
00:10:25,689 --> 00:10:26,809
I finished my food.

232
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:28,330
Don't eat this.

233
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:30,850
Wait for me.

234
00:10:32,602 --> 00:10:33,498
(Joyful and Carefree)

235
00:10:43,529 --> 00:10:46,210
That's why
Fourth Prince keeps disappearing.

236
00:10:46,210 --> 00:10:48,210
So he's been fooling around out there.

237
00:10:48,970 --> 00:10:49,889
Young Lord.

238
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:51,730
Why do I feel

239
00:10:51,809 --> 00:10:54,130
that she is much older
than the Fourth Prince?

240
00:10:54,169 --> 00:10:56,889
Yeah, and she's not so pretty.

241
00:10:56,889 --> 00:10:57,889
She is also tall and strong.

242
00:10:57,970 --> 00:10:59,250
So freaky.

243
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:02,450
But she's really polite.

244
00:11:02,809 --> 00:11:03,529
Indeed.

245
00:11:04,450 --> 00:11:06,529
Young Lord, what do we do next?

246
00:11:08,529 --> 00:11:09,490
You're asking me?

247
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:11,169
Who's the adviser here, you or me?

248
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:12,049
Right.

249
00:11:12,889 --> 00:11:14,370
At least, we know that

250
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:16,610
the Fourth Prince is into that lady.

251
00:11:18,569 --> 00:11:20,850
Well, the Fourth Prince is in love

252
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:22,569
with that girl's sister.

253
00:11:22,569 --> 00:11:23,649
My goodness.

254
00:11:24,289 --> 00:11:25,409
Which girl?

255
00:11:25,649 --> 00:11:27,689
Are you referring to the "Heroine"?

256
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:29,569
How do you know?

257
00:11:29,929 --> 00:11:32,210
Young Lord, you also
hold grudges against her?

258
00:11:32,370 --> 00:11:33,289
Not exactly.

259
00:11:34,769 --> 00:11:36,130
Why did you say "also"?

260
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,169
Did I say that?

261
00:11:39,330 --> 00:11:40,210
Not important.

262
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:41,210
Young Lord.

263
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:44,090
I think we should teach her a lesson.

264
00:11:44,169 --> 00:11:45,569
That girl offended you.

265
00:11:45,610 --> 00:11:46,970
She has no manners.

266
00:11:47,049 --> 00:11:47,850
Think about it.

267
00:11:48,130 --> 00:11:50,929
She keeps showing up
in front of the Fourth Prince.

268
00:11:51,049 --> 00:11:53,049
It's so dangerous, right?

269
00:11:53,409 --> 00:11:54,970
Shouldn't we eliminate the risk

270
00:11:55,049 --> 00:11:56,529
for the Fourth Prince?

271
00:11:58,889 --> 00:12:00,529
Yeah, we should.

272
00:12:00,569 --> 00:12:04,289
But that lady
is the sister of that girl.

273
00:12:04,330 --> 00:12:04,929
But...

274
00:12:05,169 --> 00:12:07,409
But we should
give her a warning at least.

275
00:12:07,689 --> 00:12:09,970
She shouldn't act willfully just because

276
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:11,529
the Fourth Prince likes her sister.

277
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:13,529
She'd better behave

278
00:12:13,529 --> 00:12:15,169
when she's dealing with us.

279
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:18,210
It makes sense.

280
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:21,809
Let's do this.

281
00:12:21,850 --> 00:12:23,730
Mr. Li, convey my message now.

282
00:12:24,970 --> 00:12:25,850
Me?

283
00:12:26,689 --> 00:12:27,289
I...

284
00:12:31,210 --> 00:12:32,809
You brought your daughter here?

285
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:38,450
Hello, Mrs. Chun.

